💪🔥🌱It's a bit wintery today in England...so I've just made this amazingly comforting, warming and healthy vegan Mushroom stew🌱🔥💪
1 lb. portobello or cremini mushrooms, stemmed and coarsely chopped
1 large onion, coarsely chopped
2 celery stalks, chopped
2 carrots, sliced
3 garlic cloves, minced
1 cup dry red wine
1/4 cup all-purpose flour
4 cups vegetable broth
2 tbsp. tomato paste
2 lb. red potatoes, chopped into 1-2 inch chunks
3 tbsp. fresh thyme leaves
2 tbsp. chopped fresh rosemary
1 tsp. liquid smoke
1-2 tsp. Marmite (optional, but highly recommended for savory flavor)
salt and pepper to taste
Throw it all together and simmer for 40 minutes.

These are the types of people I LOVE to work with. 
Esther has a hair appointment just before our training session. While "most" people would use this as an excuse not to give the rest of your body and mind the attention it deserves. Esther didn't even think twice. 
Training in the middle of Sevenoaks up at the Vine, Esther had a smile on her face, and put the same on others. 
With all those clips in she still put her absolute best effort to help improve her strength, mobility and flexibility. Thus helping her look and feel amazing. 
If you want it bad enough you will do whatever it takes. And it why wouldn't you. Your body desserves the BEST. 
Each day I wake up to inspire with a smile on my face. But it's times like these I can't help but to literally laugh out loud and realise the incredible people I help. 
I love you guys!

data.text: Because its a win-win...i became healthier..lost 39ibs...vegan is cheaper ..you save money and your spare life of animals too....everyone is happy !!!👍😄😄😄 been vegan since october 2016

About 25 years ago I started travelling a lot and couldn't find meat that tasted good on a budget so cut out meat , then a few years later cut out fish . I stopped dairy when I was a teen and my exczema disappeared . Been animal free now for 22 years and feel better and look better than a lot of my peers and the food is WAY yummier and you have to really eat variety to get all the nutrients you need so it's fun too :) . Gave up sugar 5 years ago too ... My only vices now are wine and the gym ;) :) vegan yummy life !

When you're aiming to hit peak happiness, we all have things that tickle us in different ways. 
My happiness could be your hell. 
However time can also turn hell into happiness. 
This time last year I wanted to test out what a vegan diet was like. 
I wanted to see how it made me feel. 
The thought of doing so was like hell. I had so many pre conceived ideas as to what it would be like. All negative may I add. 
One year later I am still vegan. I have more energy than ever, I'm stronger fitter and leaner than before. 
Now I'm not saying you should go vegan. 
All I'm saying is. Keep an open mind. 
In this modern day and age. We like to live in a world that reinforces our beliefs. Not contradict them. 
We put ourselves in a so called echo chamber. 
I have met so many happy and unhappy people doing the amazing job that I do. 
And there's one thing in common. 
The happiest all have open minds to new ideas, not scared of change and will to deal with failure when it happens instead of avoid it. 
Once that door has opened, you open yourself up to a world of adventure, happiness and excitement. 
You will be tested along the way. But you will never look back. 
Educate and Dominate

data.text: It's been almost two months for me and oh how I miss cod n chips more than I thought I ever would....oh and cheese. I really miss cheese....a brie and grape baguette or a tomato and cheddar sarnie....the whole vegan cheese thing doesn't excite me at all...on the flip side, I ordered a bunch of organic fruit and veg online from Real Foods and it makes me feel good that I'm no longer eating  gmo's and I've also cut a huge amount of processed foods out of my diet and replaced it with stuff like chia seeds, fresh fruit juices and alkaline water....although, not tried the spirulina yet I must admit, it smells rank 😜
